According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysis Division) of the Capital Policy, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August this year with the support of the Best Hungary Movement, has increased the political risk of Hungary and the region from a number of points of view.
The company's "risk warning" is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of the ethnic tensions existing between the Roma and non-Jitan population of Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic clashes can occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - the representative of the research institute added.
They affirmed that this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the Roma problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the discrepancies between Gypsys and Hungarians."
This aggravates the problem, prevents normal dialogue, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, " significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially in relation to the stability and democratic development of the country."
