As well as the supposed homosexuality or mental handicap of certain victims of deportation.
Records of the concentration camps or arrest warrants established by the Gestapo had been gathered after the war for a practical purpose: to find the countrymen deported or subjected to compulsory work and, where appropriate, to give them proof of their detention, in order to open the way for their compensation.
Even today in Bad Arolsen, more than 300 permanent employees treat tens of thousands of individual petitions.
